Etymology[edit]

Borrowed from French café.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /kaˈfeː/
  • Audio
    		(file)
  • Rhymes: -eː
  • Homophone: Kaffee (only according to one pronunciation variant of that word)
  • Hyphenation: Ca‧fé

Noun[edit]

Café n (genitive Cafés, plural Cafés)

  1. a café, a coffee shop
    Synonym: Kaffeehaus
  2. coffee
    Synonym: Kaffee
